      <div xml:id="NA261-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi iravukkuṟi vilakki varaivu kaṭāyatu.
            2. talaimakaḷ iyaṟpaṭa moḻintatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is how the confidante urges for marriage, blocking the night tryst, when [HE] is behind the fence. 2. It is also what SHE says so that [HIS] qualities would appear.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA261">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aruḷilar vāḻi tōḻi miṉṉuvaci</l>
<l>            piruṭūṅku vicumpi ṉatiru mēṟoṭu</l>
<l>            veñcuṭar karanta kamañcūl vāṉa</l>
<l>            neṭumperuṅ kuṉṟattuk kuṟumpala maṟukit</l>
<l>            tāvil perumpeya ṟalaiiya yāmattuk </l>
<l>            kaḷiṟakap paṭutta peruñciṉa mācuṇam</l>
<l>            veḷiṟil kāḻmaram piṇittunaṉi miḷiruñ</l>
<l>            cāntam pōkiya tēṅkamaḻ viṭarmukai</l>
<l>            yeruvai naṟumpū nīṭiya</l>
<l>            peruvaraic ciṟuneṟi varuta lāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>He [is] without consideration, oh friend,</l>
<l rend="indent2">for coming by the small path in the great mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the fragrant flowers on the reed have grown long by the</l>
<l rend="indent">clefts [and] caves fragrant with honey come from(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">cāntam pōkiya</term>: here we have a rare usage of <term xml:lang="ta">pō</term>, for the diffusion of fragrance.</note> the sandal,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the big angry python that had swallowed an elephant bull</l>
<l rend="indent">coils [itself] firmly around a tree with a core that is not soft(?),<note place="foot">Here T.V.G. asserts that there is a topos of <term xml:lang="ta">mācuṇam</term> snakes swallowing elephants (for which see also NA 14.8). He, however, understands line 7 in a different way, namely that the snake would shatter the elephant against the hard sandal tree before devouring it, something I cannot find in the text at all.</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">at midnight that offered faultless great rain,</l>
<l rend="indent2">the short many of fully pregnant clouds whirling</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the long big hills, hiding the hot glow</l>
<l rend="indent3">with [thunder-]strokes that shake the sky hung in darkness,</l>
<l rend="indent4">split by lightning.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
